- The request body may contain any combination of these fields. If present, they are used to update the corresponding user properties; if not present, existing values are retained.
- In Swagger 2.0, describing a JSON body payload is done using a parameter with in: body and a schema describing the allowed fields. Since the task requires Parameter Objects only and no $ref references, we inline the schema rather than referencing a predefined model.
- The endpoint is private (requires authentication via cookies), but the parameter object specification requested here focuses on the request payload itself. Security/authorization details are not included in the parameter objects as requested.
- Therefore, the Parameter Object for paths["/api/users/profile"]["PUT"].parameters will describe a single body parameter named profile with a schema containing the possible fields: name (string), email (string with email format), and password (string). Because the API supports partial updates, the body payload may omit some fields; thus, the body parameter is required at the operation level, but the individual fields within the body schema are optional (not explicitly marked as required inside the schema).

